tourBios.carHigh:
2014: Finished T114 at Web.com Tour Qualifying Tournament in December...On the Web.com Tour, competed in 17 Regular Season tournaments and made five cuts. Best finish was a T23 at the Chile Classic in March. Was 161st on the money list at season's end.

2011: Made two cuts in six starts on the Canadian Tour, with his best finish a tie for 40th at The Western Championship. Missed the cut in his first career PGA TOUR start, the Northern Trust Open. 

2010: Made the cut in four of six starts on the Web.com Tour. In his fourth start of the year he posted his first top-10 finish, at the WNB Golf Classic. Was T10 after shooting a 4-under 68 in the first round. Fired a second-round 67 and third-round 68 to be solo second after each round. Was in the final group Sunday, one stroke back. Shot 71 to finish T8.

2009: Made eight cuts in 10 starts on the PGA TOUR Canada, with a season-best T17 at the Seaforth Country Classic. 

2008: Missed the cut in his first career start on the Web.com Tour at the Northeast Pennsylvania Classic...On the Adams Golf Tour, won the Texarkana Open...Also played on the Golden State Tour.

2007: Played on the Golden State Tour. 

2006: Played the Adams Golf Tour, winning the Rising Star Open.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Winner of the 2007 Big West Championship while at Long Beach State...Four-time All-Big West selection...Was four-time MVP of high school golf team.
tourBios.personal: Attended Mayfair High School in Lakewood, Calif...His sister, Kelsey, is also a graduate of Long Beach State...Biggest thrill outside of golf is earning a college degree...The course he would most like to play is Augusta National...His favorite TV show is "PTI."...Enjoys hummus, watching Tiger Woods play and following Major League Baseball's Los Angeles Angels and the NFL's Denver Broncos...Favorite entertainer is Toby Keith...If not a professional golfer, would be a restaurant-bar owner...Biggest thrill outside golf was throwing out the first pitch at a Long Beach State Dirtbag game...Favorite course played is Riviera CC...Favorite athlete is Kobe Bryant...Not many people know he's lefthanded. Says his first-tee introduction song would be "Not Afraid" by Eminem...Twitter name is @lederergolf.

tourBios.otherInfo: Captured the Long Beach City championship and Big West Conference title

dyn.dynResults: His best finish on the Web.com Tour was T8th in 2010 at the WNB Golf Classic.
